# PostHog analytics.
# Use the app's PROD project key here (NOT a separate website project) so the
# marketing site and the app report into one project — this is what enables the
# website -> app conversion funnel. Website events are tagged surface=marketing-website
# so they stay distinguishable from the app's web/android/ios surfaces.
# The project API key is public/safe to expose in client code, hence the PUBLIC_ prefix.
# Copy this file to `.env` for local dev, and set the same vars in
# Netlify → Site settings → Environment variables for production.
# Leave PUBLIC_POSTHOG_KEY empty to disable analytics entirely (the script no-ops).
# PUBLIC_POSTHOG_HOST is optional; production routes through the /ingest proxy.

PUBLIC_POSTHOG_KEY=
PUBLIC_POSTHOG_HOST=https://eu.i.posthog.com
